The Ambassador of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia  to Nigeria H.E Adnan bin Mahmood Bustaji on Thursday met with  the  Acting Chairman of the  Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ( EFCC), Mr. Ibrahim Magu on how to assist the nation in its anti-corruption war. The envoy  discussed  with Magu the ways of mutual cooperation between Saudi Arabia And Nigeria in combating corruption and malpractices. A statement from the embassy said the Ambassador commended the efforts of the EFCC in fighting corruption in Nigeria. He wish the commission’s boss  success in his job. On his part  Magu commended the Leadership of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in combating corruption decisively through the  establishment of Anti-Corruption Agency. He said he is hopeful that Nigeria will benefit from the wide experience of the Kingdom in curbing corruption. 